            "summary": "UK and EU leaders declared a \"new chapter\" in relations during a summit in London. British PM Keir Starmer hosted EU Council President Costa and Commission President von der Leyen. The meeting sealed a \"strategic partnership,\" resetting ties post-Brexit referendum in 2016, which led to a 4% drop in economic productivity and a predicted 15% decline in trade. The summit focused on moving beyond Brexit debates toward pragmatic cooperation. Trade agreements were reached to ease post-Brexit red tape on food and agricultural trade, and European fishing vessels were granted extended access to UK waters until 2038, sparking mixed reactions. This reset was lauded by business leaders and pro-Europe lawmakers as a \"positive first step\" in rebuilding ties.",
